tafsir[10]{c,v,t}:
  89,26,"Neither will anyone bind in chains like His binding of the disbelievers in chains."
  89,29,"“Now enter along with My pious servants.”"
  90,1,"Allah takes an oath on the sacred city i.e. Makkah Al-Mukarramah"
  90,7,"Does this person boastful over the wealth he has spent think that Allah does not see him? And that He will not take him to account over his wealth: how he earned it and where he spent it?"
  90,8,"Did I not create eyes for him with which he can see?"
  90,9,"And a tongue and lips with which he can speak?"
  90,10,"And I made the paths of goodness and evils known to him."
  90,13,"It is to free a male or female slave."
  90,16,"Or a poor person who has no possessions."
  90,18,"Those are the people of the right."